{"word":"ἄλυπος","slug":"ἄλυπος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἄλυπος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:λύπη'><el>λύπη</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>without pain</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <el>ἄλ. γήρως</el> <i>without the pains</i> of age, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>; <el>τὸ ἄλυπον  ἀλυπία</el>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>—<a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a>, <el>ἀλύπως ζῆν</el> to live <i>free from pain</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <i>not paining, causing no pain</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}